19#include <vector>
20#include <memory>
21
22namespace ZXing {
23
24class Result;
25class Reader;
26class BinaryBitmap;
27class DecodeHints;
28
29/**
30* MultiFormatReader is a convenience class and the main entry point into the library for most uses.
31* By default it attempts to decode all barcode formats that the library supports. Optionally, you
32* can provide a hints object to request different behavior, for example only decoding QR codes.
33*
34* @author Sean Owen
35* @author dswitkin@google.com (Daniel Switkin)
36*/
37class MultiFormatReader
38{
39public:
40 explicit MultiFormatReader(const DecodeHints& hints);
41 ~MultiFormatReader();
42
43 Result read(const BinaryBitmap& image) const;
44
45private:
46 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<Reader>> _readers;
47};
48
49} // ZXing
